<section id="process">
    <img id="process--image" src="/grpexample.webp" width="700" height="1500" alt="green ground penetrating radar output example showing waves in the earth."/>
    <div id="process--steps">
        <div id="process--steps--title">
            <h2>Our Process</h2>
            <div class="span"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step--icon"><img src="consultation.svg" loading="lazy" alt="Two chat bubbles."></div>
            <h3>Consultation</h3>
            <p>TerraSearch Geophysical tailors each survey to meet our clients individual needs. Contact us and we will prepare a scope of work for your project, at no charge, to conduct the requested survey. All survey work will be designed to comply with local, state, and federal regulations including any necessary permits.</p> 
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step--icon" id="research--step"><img src="research.svg" loading="lazy" alt="Magnifying lense over papers."></div>
            <h3>Background Research</h3>
            <p>We conduct background research about all project areas prior to implementation of a survey, to ensure that we are providing our clients with the most appropriate survey techniques. This background research is incorporated into the survey design, implementation, and report preparation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step--icon" id="onsite--step"><img src="onsite.svg" loading="lazy" alt="Pin with a man in it pointing to a map."></div>
            <h3>On Site Work</h3>
            <p>Conduct the predetermined surveys at the project location. Depending on project scope, data collection may require multiple days/weeks of fieldwork.</p>
         </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step--icon" id="data--step"><img src="data.svg" loading="lazy" alt="Computer showing line graph."></div>
            <h3>Data Analysis and Report Preparation</h3>
            <p>Following the collection of background research and field data, a companion report will be prepared that discusses location and natural condition of the project area (e.g., topography, soils, and noted disturbances), history of the project area, the methods used during survey, and the results of the investigation.</p>
        </div> 
    </div>
</section>

<style>
    #process{
        width: 100%;
        display:grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
        background-color: rgba(40, 66, 31, 1);
    }

    #process--image {
        width:100%;
        height: 100%;
        object-fit: cover;
    }

    #process--steps{
        width: 100%;
        padding:64px 120px;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
    }

    #process--steps--title{
        align-self:flex-start;
        margin-bottom:48px;
        margin-left:60px;
    }

    #process--steps--title > h2 {
        font-size: 3rem;
        font-weight: 400;
        color:#fff;
    }

    #process--steps--title > .span {
        height:2px;
        width:95%;
        margin:2px auto 0 auto;
        background-color: rgba(254, 127, 45, 1);
    }

    .step{
        border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(254, 127, 45, 1);
        padding: 48px 120px 0 120px;
        position: relative;
    }

    .step > .step--icon {
        position: absolute;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        width:160px;
        height:160px;
        background-color:rgba(40, 66, 31, 1);
        border: 2px solid rgba(254, 127, 45, 1);
        border-radius: 50%;
        left:-80px;
        top: 50%;
        transform: translate(0,-50%);
        padding:18px;
    }

    .step > .step--icon > img {
        height:100%;
        width: 100%;
    }

    #research--step {
        padding:24px 32px 24px 16px;
    }

    #data--step {
        padding:32px 28px 24px 28px;
    }

    #onsite--step {
        padding:20px 24px 28px 24px;
    }

    .step:nth-child(3) > .step--icon , .step:nth-child(5) > .step--icon {
        left: auto;
        right: -80px;
    }

    .step:nth-child(2) {
        padding-top:0px;
    }


    .step:nth-child(2) ,  .step:nth-child(4){
        border-left: 2px solid rgba(254, 127, 45, 1);
    }

    .step:nth-child(3){
        border-right: 2px solid rgba(254, 127, 45, 1);
    }

    .step:nth-child(5){
        border-right: 2px solid rgba(254, 127, 45, 1);
        border-bottom:none;
    }

    .step > h3{
        color: #fff;
        font-size: 1.8rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }
    .step > p {
        color:#fff;
        font-size: 1rem;
        max-width: 585px;
        line-height: 2rem;
        padding:24px 0 48px 0;
    }

    @media only screen and (max-width: 800px) {
        #process{
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;;
        }

        #process > img {
            display: none;
        }

        #process--steps{
            padding:64px 16px 64px 64px;
        }

        #process--steps--title > h2 {
            font-size: 32px;
        }

        #process--steps--title{
            margin-left:0px;
        }

        .step {
            border-bottom: none;
            border-right: none !important;
            border-left:2px solid rgba(254, 127, 45, 1);
            padding: 0px 0px 0 64px;
        }

        .step > .step--icon{ 
            height: 104px;
            width: 104px;
            /* top: 96px; */
            right: auto !important;
            left:-52px !important;
            padding:12px;
        }

        #research--step {
            padding:16px 22px 20px 12px;
        }

        #onsite--step {
            padding:12px 16px 20px 16px;
        }

        #data--step {
            padding:20px 12px 16px 12px;
        }
    }



</style>